@node intro "Introduction"

 What is it for?

       This  has  been   made   primarily  for   Finnish  users.
       The Poem generates nice random poems (small stories) for screen.
       ATTENTION! You need KickStart 2.04 or higher.

@endnode

@node word "Word-File"

 Each five group contains:

       Adjective, substantive, verb, adverb and object.
       Look at Words.Txt <- Sorry, it is for Finnish users :)

       If someone writes english words (I am too lazy), please
       @{"mail file" link contact} to me and I publish it at the next release.

@endnode

@node using "Using"

 Here is some help for setting up POEM:
 
 CLI:
 
    Usage: Poem <Words path and name>
    Option -p: One poem without headers (for Dialog logout file).

 Example #1: Poem Doors:Words.Txt
         #2: Poem Doors:Words.Txt -p


 Dialog:

       2. Executable: Doors:Poem/Poem Doors:Poem/Words.Txt
       4. Description: DiaPoem V2.0
       5. Type: Executable
       6. Help file: Doors/P
      10. Load type: OVERLAY
      12. Pend messages: YES
      13. Cli mode: YES
      14. Pause: NO

@endnode

